c Systems has acquired the Liverpool, N.Y.-basedsystems division of Genigraphics for $21.1 million, Pansophic officials said.andO;The division manufactures and markets a variety of presentation graphicssoftware, workstations and peripherals.andM;Sony Corp. of America, based in Park Ridge, N.J., has signed a deal to supply$3.5 million worth of 5-1/4-inch rewritable optical storage products to U.S.andO;Design of Lanham, Md.andP;  U.S.andP;  Design will offer three Sony-based Q-Storrewritable systems.andO;</TEXT></DOC>